TAKING ON THE TYCOONS
---------------------
Every tycoon is rated in the simulation by their ability as a builder,
financier, operator and robber. Each of these four skills goes from a scale
of zero (poor) to four (excellent). For instance, the financier number
affects the rate paid for bond interest in comparison to yours (zero pays
2% more, two pays the same, four pays 2% less). Higher skill ratings
increase the likelihood of takeover attempts and rate war attacks by that
tycoon. With their high financier and robber ratings, Baron Rothschild and
George Hudson are perhaps the deadliest opposition in Railroad Tycoon. 



